<h3><span>About </span> Swar Utsav</h3>

<ol class="about_list" style="margin:0; padding:0;">
	<li>Swar Utsav was started in 2000 to celebrate 25 Years of The India Today Group</li>
    <li>Held for the first year in Central Park Connaught Place and then at the iconic India Gate. Spread first over a week and later 3 Days Swarutsav  became the most anticipated cultural event in Delhi, both amongst music lovers and artists</li>
    <li>All The Big Maestro'S of Indian Classical, Sufi, Fusion , Ghazal and Various other genres have performed on this Stage</li>
    <li>The Platform was also given to many new and upcoming artistes who are now big names. Wadali Brothers, Chhannulal Mishra, Barkat Sidhu, Kaushiki Chakraborty, Ganesh Kumaresh, all made their mark on this stage</li>
    <li>The Festival stopped with India Gate becoming a security zone but this year it is all set for its revival at the IGNCA lawns from 14th-16th November</li>
</ol>


